1095765975956373505.text: Today we say goodbye to #NASA's #Opportunity rover. Only supposed to last for 90 sol (Martian days), it lasted for 5351 sol! 1095728446842589184.text: #NASA has a planetary protection officer who reviews the instruments being sent to planets like #Mars or moons of #Saturn to make sure there are no microbes on it. 1093584504302829568.text: "I wish to be big". Ever wish you were taller? #Astronauts can grow up to 3 inches while in space! Once the #astronaut returns, their height returns to normal after a few months. pic.twitter.com/jAP9nIhQag
